      • processFolder

        protected void processFolder(MigrationPipeline pipeline,
                             MigrationQueue queue,
                             FileStoreConnection fsConnection,
                             java.lang.String relativeFolderPath)
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Lists all the files and directories for the folder passed into the parameters, processing them to add into the queue. All files inside the given directory will be added into the queue. Any sub directories found inside the folder will be processed recursively if the flag processFoldersRecursively is set to true, and the method will call itself, passing the child directory as the new parameter.
        Parameters:
        {MigrationPipeline} - pipeline
        {MigrationQueue} - queue
        {FileStoreConnection} - file or folder that will be processed
        {String} - relativeFolderPath Relative root path to the provided folder, if applicable
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown if there is an exception when processing a file to add to the queue.

      • processRow

        protected void processRow(MigrationQueue queue,
                          java.lang.String[] row,
                          int rowNum)
        This method will process the current CSV row that is being added to the queue. It will iterate through the property columns injected or defaulted by the module found on the propertyColumns variable. The method will extract the value according to the configured data type and add it to the extra properties maps used to create a new queue item. If the current row's identified source id value is unique and hasn't been added to the passed in key value set HashSet, a new queue item will be created.
        Parameters:
        {MigrationQueue} - queue
        {Set - set used to ensure no queue items with duplicate source ids are created
        {String[]} - current row we are processing
        {int} - number of the row we are processing
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
